00:21:50,309 --> 00:21:52,519
a happy, great life ahead of you,
Jeong-eun.

264
00:21:54,521 --> 00:21:56,773
You deserve to be happy. You really do.

265
00:22:28,638 --> 00:22:29,890
Are you sad?

266
00:22:45,447 --> 00:22:46,573
I always felt bad,

267
00:22:50,035 --> 00:22:51,203
so I'm happy for her.

268
00:23:00,921 --> 00:23:02,089
Thank you, Mom.

269
00:23:24,069 --> 00:23:25,654
Is Jang-mul good to you?

270
00:23:26,696 --> 00:23:28,406
My gosh, what did you say?

271
00:23:28,949 --> 00:23:29,950
What are you saying?

272
00:23:30,033 --> 00:23:32,202
Come on. I saw everything.

273
00:23:32,285 --> 00:23:34,162
What did you see? My goodness.

274
00:23:34,246 --> 00:23:35,163
Gosh.

275
00:23:36,998 --> 00:23:38,875
What on earth are you talking about?

276
00:23:38,959 --> 00:23:40,877
-I saw everything.
-Goodness.

277
00:23:45,382 --> 00:23:46,967
I have high standards, you see.

278
00:24:08,822 --> 00:24:09,656
<i>He's not here.</i>

279
00:24:20,917 --> 00:24:22,169
<i>He isn't here either.</i>

280
00:24:31,845 --> 00:24:33,096
TAESIN GROUP

281
00:24:34,181 --> 00:24:35,265
<i>Ji Cheong-sin.</i>

282
00:24:36,474 --> 00:24:37,767
<i>Where on earth is he?</i>

283
00:25:16,598 --> 00:25:19,184
You see, hope is…

284
00:25:19,768 --> 00:25:22,646
It's such a cruel beast.

285
00:25:24,314 --> 00:25:25,148
I know,

286
00:25:26,399 --> 00:25:29,236
but it's what keeps us going.

287
00:25:44,417 --> 00:25:46,670
My, look at this mansion.

288
00:25:46,753 --> 00:25:48,463
What a nice house.

289
00:25:49,589 --> 00:25:51,174
Will Hang-gyu be okay though?

290
00:25:52,175 --> 00:25:53,802
Come on. I'm sure he has a plan.

291
00:25:53,885 --> 00:25:55,595
You know the kind of person he is.

292
00:25:55,679 --> 00:25:58,265
He told us not to worry,
so we have nothing to worry about.

293
00:25:59,683 --> 00:26:03,395
But why did the chairman tell us
to come all the way to Mayor Shin's place?

294
00:26:04,854 --> 00:26:07,065
My brother is taking the fall for him,

295
00:26:07,148 --> 00:26:09,442
so I guess he wants
to give us something in return.

296
00:26:14,572 --> 00:26:16,908
My brother must've already
cut a deal with him.

297
00:26:43,935 --> 00:26:45,353
Why is it so dark in here?

298
00:26:51,693 --> 00:26:52,777
Is he over there?

299
00:27:10,503 --> 00:27:13,131
-Mr. Mayor, I heard you asked for us.
-Hello, sir.

300
00:27:15,467 --> 00:27:16,593
Is he not at home?

301
00:27:17,260 --> 00:27:18,845
-Jeez.
-My gosh.

302
00:28:53,982 --> 00:28:56,067
<i>We cannot let anyone find out about us</i>

303
00:28:56,651 --> 00:28:59,195
<i>until we've fully recovered.</i>

304
00:29:04,784 --> 00:29:05,702
What do you want?

305
00:29:06,202 --> 00:29:08,413
You… You're back.

306
00:29:58,296 --> 00:30:00,215
<i>We should eat up that punk too.</i>

307
00:30:05,261 --> 00:30:06,721
No, don't touch him.

308
00:30:07,430 --> 00:30:09,849
<i>Why not? Because he's your son?</i>

309
00:30:11,601 --> 00:30:15,814
<i>That little prick tried to kill you</i>
<i>at the hospital.</i>

310
00:30:15,897 --> 00:30:17,023
<i>I bet you had no idea.</i>

311
00:30:19,150 --> 00:30:21,069
Still, we can't kill him yet.

312
00:30:22,111 --> 00:30:23,238
Now isn't the time.

313
00:30:24,405 --> 00:30:25,573
No, not yet.

314
00:31:19,919 --> 00:31:22,922
<i>Are you really gone?</i>

315
00:31:24,173 --> 00:31:25,216
<i>Are you, Mom?</i>

316
00:31:26,509 --> 00:31:28,261
<i>Is it really true, Dad?</i>

317
00:31:35,935 --> 00:31:38,146
Hey, you said your dad is at home.

318
00:31:38,229 --> 00:31:40,148
Ask him for more pocket money.

319
00:31:41,190 --> 00:31:43,401
-Hey.
-Say something!

320
00:31:44,319 --> 00:31:45,194
What are you doing?

321
00:31:57,290 --> 00:31:58,291
Get up.

322
00:32:24,442 --> 00:32:26,736
-What?
-Your father, Shin Myeong-hwi…

323
00:32:28,446 --> 00:32:29,697
Where is he now?

324
00:32:30,657 --> 00:32:32,700
-What?
-Where is he?

325
00:33:09,487 --> 00:33:10,613
<i>It's them.</i>

326
00:33:11,531 --> 00:33:12,657
<i>No, not yet.</i>

327
00:33:12,740 --> 00:33:14,450
<i>Right now, we mustn't get caught.</i>

328
00:33:33,386 --> 00:33:34,679
Mun, stop.

329
00:33:34,762 --> 00:33:35,763
Ha-na.

330
00:33:35,847 --> 00:33:38,016
-In there--
-Can't you feel it?

331
00:33:38,099 --> 00:33:39,767
Shin Myeong-hwi isn't there now.

332
00:33:40,852 --> 00:33:41,978
He's already fled.

333
00:33:50,987 --> 00:33:52,155
Shin Myeong-hwi.

334
00:33:53,740 --> 00:33:55,616
That human trash.

335
00:33:55,700 --> 00:33:57,827
I can't believe
the evil spirit went to him.

336
00:33:57,910 --> 00:33:59,996
We're dealing with pure evil here.

337
00:34:00,079 --> 00:34:03,207
But I wonder why he's been quiet
all this time.

338
00:34:03,708 --> 00:34:06,419
No movement detected so far,
as if he's in hiding.

339
00:34:06,502 --> 00:34:10,339
That's because he now knows
we can trap him using the barrier.

340
00:34:14,177 --> 00:34:16,596
Mun, I'm sure we can find

341
00:34:17,263 --> 00:34:18,389
Shin Myeong-hwi.

342
00:34:19,182 --> 00:34:20,141
We'll track him down.

343
00:34:21,893 --> 00:34:23,186
I'm not upset.

344
00:34:25,063 --> 00:34:25,897
I'm happy.

345
00:34:27,023 --> 00:34:28,775
This means we still have a chance.

346
00:34:29,942 --> 00:34:32,361
I'm happy to know it's not over yet.

347
00:34:40,536 --> 00:34:41,954
EONNI'S NOODLES

348
00:34:42,038 --> 00:34:45,792
First, let's find out
where Shin Myeong-hwi could be hiding.

349
00:34:46,542 --> 00:34:48,503
His son is that kid at your school, right?

350
00:34:48,586 --> 00:34:49,712
Yes.

351
00:34:49,796 --> 00:34:51,422
He must have a vacation home.

352
00:34:52,215 --> 00:34:53,174
I'll find out.

353
00:34:55,468 --> 00:34:57,303
-Look who's here.
-My gosh!

354
00:34:57,386 --> 00:34:59,305
-Hi, So-eun.
-So-eun.

355
00:34:59,388 --> 00:35:00,515
-Hello.
-Hello.

356
00:35:00,598 --> 00:35:02,934
Hi, So-eun. What brings you here?

357
00:35:03,017 --> 00:35:06,687
So-eun is doing a lot better now.
She missed you, Mun.

358
00:35:06,771 --> 00:35:08,356
-My gosh.
-We came for some noodles,

359
00:35:08,439 --> 00:35:10,608
-but I guess you're closed today?
-Oh.

360
00:35:10,691 --> 00:35:12,735
His brother is Kwon Jin-seung
at Love Jungjin.

361
00:35:12,819 --> 00:35:14,403
-Oh, I see.
-Hello, I'm Kwon Jin-ho.

362
00:35:15,113 --> 00:35:16,531
This is his brother's daughter.

363
00:35:16,614 --> 00:35:19,408
Hello, I'm Kwon So-eun.

364
00:35:19,492 --> 00:35:22,703
My gosh, you're So-eun.
It's so nice to meet you.

365
00:35:23,871 --> 00:35:25,915
-Mo-tak, boil water for some noodles.
-Okay.

366
00:35:25,998 --> 00:35:27,750
-It's cold. Come on in.
-Thank you.

367
00:35:27,834 --> 00:35:28,918
-Come on in.
-All right.

368
00:35:29,460 --> 00:35:31,879
Have some noodles. Here you go.

369
00:35:32,421 --> 00:35:33,923
-Thank you.
-Here's yours, So-eun.

370
00:35:37,051 --> 00:35:38,719
Here, I'll stir it for you.

371
00:35:39,512 --> 00:35:41,389
My gosh, I'm very glad to see So-eun

372
00:35:41,472 --> 00:35:42,598
looking so healthy.

373
00:35:43,891 --> 00:35:45,143
I'm proud of her.

374
00:35:45,226 --> 00:35:47,103
I'm relieved that she's doing better now,

375
00:35:47,186 --> 00:35:49,105
but a lot of the kids
are still struggling.

376
00:35:50,523 --> 00:35:53,901
That's no surprise. They drank
and bathed in that water for so long.

377
00:35:54,777 --> 00:35:56,863
Are those jerks at Taesin
still playing dumb?

378
00:35:56,946 --> 00:36:00,408
Yes. But thanks to your help,
we have many supporters now.

379
00:36:00,992 --> 00:36:04,787
As soon as we have the results
from So-eun's heavy metals analysis,

380
00:36:04,871 --> 00:36:06,414
we'll schedule a press conference.

381
00:36:07,498 --> 00:36:09,750
Good. We're really almost there now.

382
00:36:09,834 --> 00:36:12,211
You see, about the press conference…

383
00:36:12,295 --> 00:36:13,796
Do it at my hotel.

384
00:36:14,380 --> 00:36:16,340
Let's use the media to our advantage.

385
00:36:16,424 --> 00:36:19,177
We should really take down
those scumbags once and for all.

386
00:36:19,260 --> 00:36:21,929
He loves to spend a ton of money
for a good cause.

387
00:36:23,014 --> 00:36:25,224
-What? I do?
-Yes, a hell of a lot of money.

388
00:36:26,517 --> 00:36:27,852
Watch it. There's a kid here.

389
00:36:27,935 --> 00:36:29,228
Oh, my bad.

390
00:36:29,312 --> 00:36:30,855
-Forget what I said.
-Eat up.

391
00:37:27,620 --> 00:37:29,872
If they insist that the kid's body
is evidence

392
00:37:30,498 --> 00:37:32,667
and living proof in and of itself,

393
00:37:34,168 --> 00:37:36,712
the ICT project will face
yet another roadblock.

394
00:37:37,213 --> 00:37:39,840
I think environmental organizations
have their backs.

395
00:37:42,510 --> 00:37:45,596
A kid who's bound to die should just die.

396
00:37:49,642 --> 00:37:51,727
But Hang-gyu and Chang-gyu aren't around,

397
00:37:52,979 --> 00:37:55,439
so I have no one to entrust
with such a task.

398
00:38:13,040 --> 00:38:15,167
What do I do? The cops are looking for me.

399
00:38:16,377 --> 00:38:20,214
Damn it! Why did that lunatic
have to shoot himself in the head?

400
00:38:24,927 --> 00:38:27,096
Hey! Turn down the TV volume!

401
00:38:27,638 --> 00:38:30,016
Do you think you own this inn?

402
00:38:30,808 --> 00:38:33,811
Jeez, are your ears plugged?

403
00:38:34,395 --> 00:38:36,063
You do this all the time.

404
00:38:36,147 --> 00:38:38,482
Do I sound like a barking dog?

405
00:38:39,317 --> 00:38:40,693
Open the door, you piece of shit!

406
00:38:46,490 --> 00:38:49,368
Hey, gorgeous. This would've been

407
00:38:49,452 --> 00:38:50,494
nice to know.

408
00:38:57,460 --> 00:38:59,920
<i>What did I say I'd do</i>
<i>if you caused trouble again?</i>

409
00:39:00,004 --> 00:39:01,714
-What? Who are you?
-I'm…

410
00:39:02,381 --> 00:39:04,008
I'm Kim Deok-sik.

411
00:39:07,303 --> 00:39:08,846
<i>I have a job for you.</i>

412
00:39:10,014 --> 00:39:11,098
What?

413
00:39:11,182 --> 00:39:12,808
You're alive?

414
00:39:13,559 --> 00:39:15,061
I want to stay alive.

415
00:39:57,228 --> 00:39:58,062
Damn it.

416
00:40:08,114 --> 00:40:08,989
Is that blood?

417
00:40:19,041 --> 00:40:20,042
What did you say?

418
00:40:20,126 --> 00:40:21,961
Your family must have a vacation home.

419
00:40:22,044 --> 00:40:23,170
Is Mayor Shin…

420
00:40:25,381 --> 00:40:28,300
I mean, your father. Where is he now?

421
00:40:28,384 --> 00:40:31,971
Well, why do you need to know?

422
00:40:32,054 --> 00:40:34,056
Because I have to meet him now.

423
00:40:36,350 --> 00:40:38,352
I'm baffled because you look so serious.

424
00:40:40,271 --> 00:40:41,439
Hey.

425
00:40:41,522 --> 00:40:43,774
You act up at school and think you're it?

426
00:40:44,608 --> 00:40:46,318
Is my dad just some guy next door?

427
00:40:46,402 --> 00:40:47,445
He has no time for you.

428
00:40:48,779 --> 00:40:49,613
Just get lost.

429
00:40:51,824 --> 00:40:52,658
Haven't you

430
00:40:53,284 --> 00:40:55,369
noticed anything different about him?

431
00:41:00,082 --> 00:41:01,000
You saw it too.

432
00:41:02,334 --> 00:41:03,461
Those eyes.

433
00:41:09,300 --> 00:41:10,217
You know

434
00:41:10,968 --> 00:41:12,094
that your dad

435
00:41:13,387 --> 00:41:14,263
is in danger now.

436
00:41:22,396 --> 00:41:24,607
Hey, So-eun. Pork or beef?

437
00:41:24,690 --> 00:41:25,524
<i>Pork.</i>

438
00:41:25,608 --> 00:41:27,401
Beef is expensive.

439
00:41:27,485 --> 00:41:28,527
Come on. It's fine.

440
00:41:29,069 --> 00:41:30,488
We'll have beef today, okay?

441
00:41:31,739 --> 00:41:33,699
Excuse me. What's good today?

442
00:41:33,782 --> 00:41:35,242
I want Korean beef, not pork.

443
00:41:42,208 --> 00:41:45,169
I see that you also hate studying.

444
00:41:48,464 --> 00:41:49,882
OUR FLIGHT WILL LAST FOREVER

445
00:42:07,650 --> 00:42:08,692
Check upstairs.

446
00:42:09,527 --> 00:42:10,528
Will do.

447
00:42:14,323 --> 00:42:15,491
He's not here.

448
00:42:23,123 --> 00:42:25,292
No sign of him
visiting this place recently.

449
00:42:25,376 --> 00:42:26,210
He's not here.

450
00:42:26,293 --> 00:42:28,337
How many vacation homes does he have?

451
00:42:28,420 --> 00:42:29,838
We don't have a lot of time.

452
00:42:31,048 --> 00:42:33,759
You see, life is tough.

453
00:42:37,012 --> 00:42:39,181
I thought you at least cared about kids.

454
00:42:39,265 --> 00:42:41,225
<i>I guess you don't anymore.</i>

455
00:42:46,647 --> 00:42:47,481
I spotted one.

456
00:42:47,565 --> 00:42:48,857
Who? Shin Myeong-hwi?

457
00:42:50,109 --> 00:42:51,277
No, Baek Hyang-hui.

458
00:42:51,360 --> 00:42:53,320
But she's with So-eun.

459
00:42:53,404 --> 00:42:55,030
So-eun? Why is she with So-eun?

460
00:42:55,656 --> 00:42:58,784
If Shin found out, he wouldn't want
the press conference to happen.

461
00:42:58,867 --> 00:43:00,202
And to do that…

462
00:43:00,828 --> 00:43:02,663
So-eun! She's in danger.

463
00:43:04,081 --> 00:43:06,458
Shit! Damn it.

464
00:43:06,542 --> 00:43:08,502
I just drove by their fog.

465
00:43:12,131 --> 00:43:14,300
Can't I just eat this kid now?

466
00:43:14,383 --> 00:43:16,927
<i>I need that kid gone without a trace.</i>

467
00:43:17,511 --> 00:43:20,931
<i>If you think you can completely</i>
<i>get rid of her, go ahead.</i>

468
00:43:22,516 --> 00:43:24,685
Do you think I'm a zombie or what?

469
00:43:26,937 --> 00:43:28,480
How could they do this to a kid?

470
00:43:29,148 --> 00:43:30,107
And she's not well.

471
00:43:30,190 --> 00:43:32,401
Think about all the things they've done.

472
00:43:32,484 --> 00:43:34,028
They're not even human.

473
00:43:34,111 --> 00:43:36,322
She was driving along Highway 26.

474
00:43:36,405 --> 00:43:38,657
Can you keep our territory up on the way?

475
00:43:38,741 --> 00:43:39,783
I'll try.

476
00:43:47,791 --> 00:43:50,753
Who would have known Shin Myeong-hwi
would be his new host?

477
00:43:50,836 --> 00:43:53,255
He couldn't have picked a better host.

478
00:43:53,922 --> 00:43:56,300
Now, he even has full control over you,
Chairman Cho.

479
00:43:59,011 --> 00:44:00,095
You're all done, right?

480
00:44:00,888 --> 00:44:01,805
Get going, then.

481
00:44:04,141 --> 00:44:05,184
Where's my pay?

482
00:44:06,143 --> 00:44:07,853
I can't leave until I get paid.

483
00:44:24,662 --> 00:44:28,540
Looks like I'll get to see some flames
today. Fun! It's been too long.

484
00:44:28,624 --> 00:44:30,668
But you're getting me a new car, right?

485
00:44:38,425 --> 00:44:39,426
Go ahead and pour it.

486
00:44:52,648 --> 00:44:53,816
Shit.

487
00:44:55,275 --> 00:44:56,485
-What is this?
-Back off!

488
00:45:22,761 --> 00:45:25,180
Damn it. Guys, whack them.

489
00:45:36,692 --> 00:45:38,986
Oh, boy. I told him to go easy on them.

490
00:45:42,698 --> 00:45:44,366
That old man's not here.

491
00:45:44,450 --> 00:45:46,493
I guess you can't use the staff
without him.

492
00:45:49,037 --> 00:45:50,706
That little girl is ill.

493
00:45:52,249 --> 00:45:54,251
How could you do this to a kid?

494
00:46:24,323 --> 00:46:25,365
Damn it.

495
00:46:28,785 --> 00:46:29,786
Shit.

496
00:46:34,583 --> 00:46:36,418
So-eun. So-eun! Are you okay?

497
00:46:37,252 --> 00:46:38,378
Mun…

498
00:46:38,462 --> 00:46:41,465
Yes, So-eun. You're safe now.

499
00:47:04,404 --> 00:47:05,572
Ga Mo-tak!

500
00:47:05,656 --> 00:47:08,283
No, I mean… Detective Ga.

501
00:47:09,201 --> 00:47:10,452
I didn't do anything.

502
00:47:11,078 --> 00:47:12,329
Shin Myeong-hwi told me--

503
00:47:16,583 --> 00:47:20,003
This is what worthless scumbags
like you deserve.

504
00:47:20,087 --> 00:47:22,047
-Detective Ga.
-This is my motto.

505
00:47:22,798 --> 00:47:24,883
"Beat them up to a pulp
but don't kill them."

506
00:47:25,509 --> 00:47:28,220
I'm one of the top 50 business tycoons
in this country--

507
00:47:29,263 --> 00:47:31,932
Even a criminal like you
is this clever and savvy.

508
00:47:32,599 --> 00:47:35,143
It makes me think
that we really need to smarten up.

509
00:47:38,981 --> 00:47:41,024
Hey, stay with me.

510
00:47:41,108 --> 00:47:43,485
No, get up. Come on.

511
00:47:43,569 --> 00:47:45,153
All right, 12 more punches to go.

512
00:47:45,237 --> 00:47:47,823
I'll make you suffer, you bastard.

513
00:47:47,906 --> 00:47:49,866
Hey, enough!

514
00:47:49,950 --> 00:47:51,201
You'll break his nose.

515
00:47:51,868 --> 00:47:54,955
It's so annoying to waste my power
on healing jerks like him.

516
00:47:55,038 --> 00:47:57,040
Well, I just couldn't control my anger.

517
00:47:57,541 --> 00:48:00,877
Hey, do you realize who
you're dealing with here? I'm Cho Tae-sin!

518
00:48:05,716 --> 00:48:08,802
It'll be a lot of work anyway.
One punch won't make a difference.

519
00:48:08,885 --> 00:48:10,012
All right!

520
00:48:14,141 --> 00:48:16,727
We'll erase these jerks' memories
as well as So-eun's

521
